				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just got done reading everyone's comments concerning the bottleneck at Ragefire and figured I would add my 2 cents.<BR>
<BR>
In all honesty Viarant and Absor are correct here.  The problem isn't the quest, it's guilds.  <BR>
<BR>
Every cleric in every uber guild has to have this item and that's the real problem.  Big raids require lots of res's.  This saves major downtime after an ugly fight and to ensure you can get online faster after the smackdown you have to have multiplues of this epic.  Therefore every cleric in the guild MUST have it.  Greed before need is now the rule so that you can get more pulls, quicker and get more uber loot.  For many in these guilds it's no longer a matter of the accomplishment of something great, because that's what the quests where meant to be, it's now I can go after more loot quicker.<BR>
<BR>
I am a cleric.  I have been playing my cleric for a year now.  I have attained 51st level with very little uber equipment or cash.  I am not in an uber guild but have had to try and out damage them at some spawns becuase uber guilds try to steal them when someone in there guild needs the item.  It doesn't matter to them that I was waiting for hours at the spawn with no one else around.  No, every spawn is theirs. If you are not in their guild and they need it, their time is more important than yours so move along and come back some other time.  This is the atitude I have experienced with uber guilds.<BR>
<BR>
Now uber guilds are fighting over this and causing grief to one another.  They are generating hard feelings amongst the mighty and are complaining becuase they can't all get the equipment for immediate gratification.  I'm sorry that you folks can't work out an issue that in all reality means nothing.  I am happy that Viarant has decided not to change anything.<BR>
<BR>
Maybe this will cause some of you frustration and maybe uber players to leave the game, but in al honesty I doubt it.  I think what it will really happen is that it will cause more Ragefire stealing and more hard feeling amongst the mighty.  Have fun if you can.<BR>

