				&quot;if I ask Verant to make me level 60, and give me the benifits of every class (SOW, Clarity, Heal etc) should they?&quot;<BR>
<BR>
No, hence the term REASONABLE change.  <BR>
<BR>
I'm not saying they should give in to every little demand, but this is a rather sought-after item that makes getting through those nasty high levels a bit easier.  It shouldn't be a cakewalk to get but it shouldn't be made so rare and difficult that it nearly sparks guild wars and unecessarily creates a hostile environment amongst the players.  This is supposed to be a game and games are supposed to be fun, and having to camp something for weeks while fighting off KSers is not my idea of fun. <BR>
<BR>
And to the person talking about the server economy, this is a no drop item and therefore has no effect on the &quot;economy&quot;.  The economy is affected when valuable items are farmed to be sold for profit.  They become less rare and therefore the prices drop. 
